<h1 class="">About the BUKMARK.CLUB</h1>
<p>
  A collection of web pages from across the Internet.
  <br><br>
  Websites must have a curated collection of bookmarks and/or links to other websites to be eligible for a listing in this directory.
</p>
<h2 class="mt2">Recent Additions</h2>
<ul class="grid grid3 gap2 my1">
{% for page in collections.latest | reverse %}
  <li class="card">
    <h3 class="h5 m0">{{ page.data.title }}</h3>
    {% if page.data.author %}
      <p class="m0">Author: {{ page.data.author }}</p>
    {% endif %}
    <p class="m0">
      <a href="{{ page.data.url }}" rel="noopener" target="_blank">[Visit Site]</a>
    </p>
  </li>
{% endfor %}
  <li class="flex justify-content-center" style="width: 100%; height: 100%;">
    <span style="align-self: center;">
      <a class="h4" href="/directory">[Browse Directory]</a>
    </span>
  </li>
</ul>
<h2 class="mt2">Joining the BUKMARK.CLUB</h2>
<p>If you're interested in getting your site added to the BUKMARK.CLUB, all you need to do is:</p>
<ol class="my1" style="list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 3rem;">
  <li>Make sure you're adding a personal website.</li>
  <li>Make sure the site offers a curated collection of bookmarks and/or links to other websites at a dedicated URL (i.e. /bookmarks, /links).</li>
  <li>Head over to <a href="https://github.com/ttntm/bukmark.club" rel="noopener" target="_blank">[our GitHub repository]</a> and create a pull request (or an issue) to add your site.</li>
  <li>We will review you PR (or issue). If everything's alright, your site will be added to the directory.</li>
</ol>
<p>You can also contact us via email at webmaster[at]bukmark[dot]club to have your website listed. Please include all necessary information (see existing listings).</p>
<p>Note: we reserve the explicit right _not_ to add submissions to the directory, and to remove submissions at any time, if we deem them unsuitable in any way.</p>
